Rating: 4
I had read that others suggested adding heat and marinating longer and that the recipe required more marinade, more sauce. I doubled the marinade and used this for only 2 boneless chicken breasts. I added a half teaspoon of red chili paste and a teaspoon of minced ginger and marinated overnight---this was not intentional it jusy worked out that way, I was careful to turn the chicken and reposition the onions every 8 hours or so. For some reason it was the onions that picked up the heat of the chili paste. I had napa cabbage, green beans,and red pepper and carrot in the fridge (had made some minestrone) so I blanched green beans then sauteed in smoking hot peanut oil w garlic, sauteed julienned carrot w a little ginger and finished w rice wine, sauteed julienned red pepper and nappa cabbage w peanut oil, sesame oil and a dash of soy, combined and sliced the finished chicken on this bed of veggies and it was great, colorful and tasty. I dusted w some black sesame seeds that also made it fun.

