Rating: 4
This dish has become a staple in my house. My toddlers love it. I have made it according to the recipe leaving the skin on the chicken and found it way to greasy and had a hard time ladeling the fat off. Also sauce didn't marinade through the skin very well, making the inside of the chicken kinda bland. There wasn't enough sauce (because everyone loves pouring extra sauce over their rice) and it was a little salty. So I now use chicken thighs with the bone in and peel off the skin and I double the sauce and omit the salt. I don't even bother marinating it. The skinless chicken soaks up all the sauce while cooking and turns a yummy color.

